snippet.textDisplay:
Like a lot of people in quarantine, I've been watching marvel movies again. A visual effect that stood out to me, amongst them all, is in Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2

Yandu has a physical fire emblem in his hand (unless it was so good it was CGI the whole time and he never had anything in his hand), the camera gets low and we see Yandu hand the emblem over to baby Groot with no cut once we are down there.
Was he holding something physical and then handed it over to nothing, and then when they make the cut down to Groot is the entire thing CGI? Yandu's hand/baby groot/emblem and all?
Or was it a movie trick of handing from real to cgi? Would love some thoughts on that scene
snippet.textOriginal:
